<TITLE> Youth arrested with weapons in Meharpur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Meharpur, Apr 28 (bdnews24.com) Police on Wednesday arrested a youth carrying weapons in Gangni upazila in Meharpur. Police alleged that Mehadi Hasan, a resident of Meherpur's Malsadah village, was the leader of the Hasan group, a criminal group of Gangni. Gangni police chief Matier Rahman told bdnews24.com that Hasan was arrested at around 1pm from his residence with a revolver. He was involved with the opposition political party BNP and had taken part in several crimes in the locality, police said. Police filed an arms case against him. bdnews24.co
